@Estee White Photography That makes sense.  Yes, since this tutorial was created, .kts files become more common.  .kts files are Kotlin Script files which do behave differently than .kt files.  The .kts files are where we can place our Gradle logic if we are using the Kotlin Gradle DSL rather than using standard Groovy in our build.gradle files.  

Within the newest IntelliJ, the New Project setup has also become a bit more confusing.  If you create a new Kotlin Console application with  "Gradle Groovy"  rather than "Gradle Kotlin" that will give a project structure that should pretty closely match what was in this older version of IntelliJ

